# No AI Attribution

## Git Commits

- NEVER add `Co-authored-by` lines referencing Cursor, AI, any agent, or any automated tool
- NEVER add any trailer, tag, or metadata attributing the commit to any AI tool
- NEVER mention Cursor, Cursor Agent, AI assistance, or any AI tool in commit messages
- Commit messages should read as if written by the developer, not an AI tool
- When creating commits, ALWAYS set both author AND committer to `Sumit Agrawal <mr.sumitagrawal.17@gmail.com>` using `GIT_COMMITTER_NAME` and `GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL` environment variables alongside `--author`
- This applies to ALL commits — initial commits, amends, rebases, and any other git operations

## Code Comments and Documentation

- NEVER add comments like "Built by Cursor Agent", "Generated by AI", or similar attribution
- NEVER include any AI branding, attribution, or mentions in source code, comments, docstrings, or documentation files
- Do not reference Cursor, Copilot, Claude, or any AI tool as the author or contributor in any file
